-- 
-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 09:52AM EDT
-- None



April 15 (Reuters) -  U.S. stock indexes opened slightly higher on Tuesday after earnings from Coca Cola and Johnson & Johnson overshadowed a mixed bag of economic data. The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> was up 0.58 percent at 16,266.94, the S&P 500 <.SPX> was up 0.69 percent at 1,843.33 and the Nasdaq Composite <.IXIC> was up 0.74 percent at 4,052.271. [.N]

** THE COCA-COLA CO <KO.N>, $39.78, +2.71 pct The beverage giant reported better-than-expected quarterly revenue as strong sales in China more than offset a drop in Europe and flat volumes in North America. [ID:nL3N0N72YU]  ** MORGAN STANLEY <MS.N>, $29.54, +1.65 pct BofA Merrill Lynch upgraded Morgan Stanley to "Buy" from "Neutral", citing better returns and lower risk after a recent downturn in the bank's stock prices. BofA Merrill added that it expects Morgan Stanley's earnings to rise in wealth management, equities, and investment banking. The stock has fallen more than 10 percent since March 20.  ** HALOZYME THERAPEUTICS INC <HALO.O>, $7.55, +5.01 pct Analysts at Citigroup started coverage on the biotechnology company with a "buy" rating and a $12 price target, saying the commercial potential of its partnerships with Roche Holding AG <ROG.VX> and Baxter International Inc <BAX.N> were higher than consensus estimates and could speed up the progress of the company to profitability. Halozyme licensed its drug delivery technology to Roche and Baxter and is entitled to receive royalties and milestone payments on sales of products developed using the technology.   "We see substantial opportunity for these products, the cash flows of which should help support the development of Halozyme's proprietary pipeline," the analysts wrote in a note.  ** PEP BOYS-MANNY, MOE & JACK <PBY.N>, $10.66, -10.94 pct The auto parts retailer reported a 7 percent drop in fourth-quarter revenue and said weak pricing is expected to hit results in the next quarter as well. [ID:nBw6zMDXda]  ** WALTER ENERGY INC <WLT.N>, $8.1, +3.85 pct The coal miner said it would idle its mines in British Columbia and temporarily lay off about 695 jobs. [ID:nL3N0N73DC]  ** AARON'S INC <AAN.N>, $28.95, -4.99 pct The rent-to-own furniture and electronics retailer rejected a $2.3 billion takeover offer from a major shareholder and instead acquired a retail credit financing firm for about $700 million. [ID:nL3N0N72SW]  ** CHARLES SCHWAB CORP <SCHW.N>, $26.08, +3.08 pct The discount broker reported a higher-than-expected quarterly profit due to a rise in trading commissions and fees for managing client assets. [ID:nL3N0N73CC]  ** JOHNSON & JOHNSON <JNJ.N>, $98.66, +1.56 pct The diversified healthcare company reported quarterly earnings well above Wall Street expectations, as strong sales of new prescription drugs offset weak sales of consumer products, and slightly raised its full-year profit view. [ID:nL2N0N70FA]  ** INFOSYS LTD <INFY.N>, $53.53, -3.69 pct Staff left India's second largest IT services exporter at an unprecedented pace in the last quarter, worrying its management and raising investors' concerns about its ability to win lucrative contracts even as it posted a higher-than-expected net profit for the period. [ID:nL3N0N70T7]  ** ENTERGY CORP <ETR.N>, $72.19, +1.75 pct The utility said its first-quarter earnings will be boosted by higher nuclear power prices, as cold winter weather and northeast pipeline infrastructure limitations boosted the demand for diverse nuclear generation units. Entergy, which supplies electricity to 2.8 million customers in Arkansas, Louisiana,  Mississippi and Texas, expects first-quarter earnings of $2.23 per share and operational earnings of about $2.28 per share. [ID:nPn9dLDml] Analysts on an average were expecting the company to earn $1.16 per share, according to Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S. Entergy will report first-quarter results on April 24.  ** RIVERBED TECHNOLOGY INC <RVBD.O>, $19.12, +1.38 pct Hedge fund Elliott Management reaffirmed its $3.36 billion offer for the network gear maker, saying it remained "extremely interested" in acquiring the company. [ID:nL3N0N73E6]  ** ZEBRA TECHNOLOGIES CORP <ZBRA.O>, $68.69, +0.60 pct ** MOTOROLA SOLUTIONS INC <MSI.N>, $63.21, -0.89 pct Barcode printer maker Zebra Technologies said it would buy Motorola Solutions's enterprise business, which makes rugged mobile computers, tablets and barcode scanners, for $3.45 billion in cash. [ID:nL3N0N72O0]   Keywords: MARKETS USA STOCKS/PULSE